WEBVTT

01:02.105 --> 01:05.108
[FAINT TRAFFIC SOUNDS]

01:05.239 --> 01:07.284
[TRAIN RATTLING]

01:14.074 --> 01:18.078
[BROODING INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

01:25.998 --> 01:29.611
MAN:
The game of kings - chess -

01:29.741 --> 01:31.917
transcends culture,

01:32.048 --> 01:34.224
religion, race, politics

01:34.355 --> 01:36.661
and economics.

01:36.792 --> 01:39.838
Doesn't matter what
your circumstances are,

01:39.969 --> 01:41.884
you can enjoy
a good old-fashioned battle

01:42.014 --> 01:45.105
over a chessboard anytime.

01:46.497 --> 01:49.544
This here's
not an ordinary game, you see.

01:49.674 --> 01:52.764
Could say
it's a high-stakes game.

01:52.895 --> 01:56.116
The highest stakes of all.

01:58.205 --> 01:59.902
This is Abe.

02:00.032 --> 02:03.035
Abe is my boss.
I drive for him.

02:03.166 --> 02:04.907
Sounds simple enough.

02:05.037 --> 02:06.561
But it ain't.

02:08.650 --> 02:10.913
You see, Abe is a gangster.

02:11.043 --> 02:12.567
Old-school.

02:12.697 --> 02:15.657
It's all about loyalty
and honour with Abe.

02:15.787 --> 02:19.617
But the thing is,
Abe suffers from DID -

02:19.748 --> 02:22.229
dissociative identity disorder.

02:23.578 --> 02:26.015
Or, in layman's terms,

02:26.146 --> 02:28.844
multiple personalities.

02:32.804 --> 02:35.198
Now, this is Frankie.

02:35.329 --> 02:38.245
Frankie is his own
sort of fuckin' crazy.

02:38.375 --> 02:40.160
Not crazy like Abe crazy,

02:40.290 --> 02:42.945
just...sociopath crazy.

02:43.075 --> 02:44.816
You see,
Frankie used to work for Abe

02:44.947 --> 02:47.645
until he decided
to do his own thing.

02:47.776 --> 02:51.606
Abe and Frankie have been
at each other ever since.

02:51.736 --> 02:55.479
The media call it a gang war.

02:55.610 --> 02:57.786
Abe calls it a problem.

02:57.916 --> 02:59.614
And Frankie?

02:59.744 --> 03:01.964
Frankie calls it business.

03:06.011 --> 03:10.015
[TENSE INDUSTRIAL ROCK MUSIC]

04:15.516 --> 04:19.911
[SIREN WAILS]

04:21.739 --> 04:23.611
MAN: Abe has been good to me.

04:23.741 --> 04:25.482
Like a father figure.

04:25.613 --> 04:27.397
A mentor.

04:27.528 --> 04:30.966
And a mate, faults and all.

04:31.140 --> 04:35.753
To be truly honest, the last
24 hours feels like a dream,

04:35.884 --> 04:37.581
and not a good one.

04:37.712 --> 04:39.279
More like a fuckin' nightmare.

04:39.409 --> 04:40.541
[MUTED CONVERSATION]

04:40.671 --> 04:44.066
None of this feels real.
But here I am.

04:44.196 --> 04:46.808
DETECTIVE: ..electronically
recorded record of interview.

04:46.938 --> 04:49.289
And, Ben, can you state
your full and correct name?

04:50.115 --> 04:51.552
Ben Michael Carter.

04:51.682 --> 04:54.642
DETECTIVE: OK. Do you go by
any other names or nicknames?

04:54.772 --> 04:56.296
- Benny.
DETECTIVE: Benny.

04:57.732 --> 04:59.560
And you understand
why you're here?

05:04.913 --> 05:08.830
OK, Ben, so we are here
because of an incident

05:08.960 --> 05:12.703
that occurred
at the Lucky Saints Bar.

05:12.877 --> 05:16.664
Can you tell me what happened
before police became involved?

05:19.275 --> 05:20.929
From which part?

05:21.059 --> 05:22.583
BEN: Let's rewind.

05:22.713 --> 05:24.498
[TAPE REWINDING]

05:24.628 --> 05:27.588
[PENSIVE PIANO MUSIC]

05:32.288 --> 05:35.335
The day started
like every other day.

05:36.553 --> 05:39.121
Wake up, you sleepyhead!
Wake up!

05:39.251 --> 05:41.341
- Wake up, wake up, wake up!
- [ABE GROANS]

05:41.471 --> 05:43.386
- You gotta get out of bed.
- Mia!

05:43.517 --> 05:46.171
Leave your father alone and
go and get ready for school.

05:46.302 --> 05:48.086
- Wake up, wake up!
- [GRUFFLY] Mia...

05:48.217 --> 05:50.132
..you just...

05:50.262 --> 05:52.090
..woke up Tickle Frankenstein!

05:52.221 --> 05:55.833
- No!
- [ABE ROARS PLAYFULLY]

05:55.964 --> 05:57.052
Tickle Frankenstein!

05:57.182 --> 05:58.706
Mia, go and get ready
for school.

05:58.836 --> 06:01.317
And, Abe, stop stirring her up.

06:01.448 --> 06:02.884
Go get dressed.

06:03.928 --> 06:06.061
You stir her up and then
I have to chill her out

06:06.191 --> 06:07.802
and get her ready for school.

06:07.932 --> 06:10.282
It's not my fault she woke up
Tickle Frankenstein.

06:10.413 --> 06:11.893
[HUFFS] Tickle Frankenstein...

06:12.023 --> 06:15.375
- Hey, Your Honour, come here.
- [CHUCKLES]

06:15.505 --> 06:18.595
Hey, Your Honour,
I'm pleading the Fifth.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.510
Mmm. You always do.

06:32.914 --> 06:34.568
- Mm-mm.
- Come on.

06:34.698 --> 06:36.744
Mm-mm. Uh-uh.

06:36.874 --> 06:39.050
- Come on.
- I've got to get ready.

06:41.270 --> 06:42.576
[GROANS SOFTLY]

06:44.055 --> 06:46.144
There's things to do.

06:51.062 --> 06:52.237
[SIGHS SOFTLY]

06:52.368 --> 06:53.587
Yep.

06:56.503 --> 06:59.462
[LOW OMINOUS MUSIC]

07:28.186 --> 07:30.885
[INDIE POP SONG
PLAYS ON STEREO]

07:31.015 --> 07:32.060
Morning, Princess.

07:33.627 --> 07:36.238
Smells awesome.

07:36.368 --> 07:38.283
Hey, don't forget
we've got dinner

07:38.414 --> 07:40.242
on Friday night
with Michelle and Ryan.

07:40.372 --> 07:42.549
Friday? Mmm...

07:44.159 --> 07:45.900
I'm just playing with you.

07:46.030 --> 07:48.859
I love hanging out
with your sister and Brian.

07:48.990 --> 07:50.774
I can see that.

07:50.905 --> 07:52.994
And it's Ryan, not Brian.

07:53.124 --> 07:56.171
Yeah, yeah, I know it's Ryan.
I'm just joking around.

07:56.301 --> 07:57.955
Friday?

07:58.086 --> 08:00.480
Friday. Locked it in.

08:00.654 --> 08:04.309
Can I go to Stephanie's
on the weekend to the movies?

08:04.396 --> 08:05.789
Abe?

08:05.920 --> 08:07.399
Fine by me.

08:09.619 --> 08:11.534
Alright, well,
I'll call Stephanie's mum

08:11.665 --> 08:13.275
- and sort something out.
- Yay!

08:13.405 --> 08:15.190
But you have to do
your homework first.

08:15.320 --> 08:18.062
- That's the deal, OK?
MIA: Yes, yes. I promise.

08:18.193 --> 08:20.195
ABE: Coffee, honey?
SOFIA: No, thanks.

08:20.325 --> 08:22.719
I'm being good and cutting down
on my caffeine.

08:22.850 --> 08:25.592
OK, you be good and all that,

08:25.722 --> 08:28.856
but you are missing out
on the Abe special brew.

08:30.031 --> 08:33.338
Special brew?
It's instant coffee.

08:33.469 --> 08:36.254
Hey, it's how you make it,
my angel.

08:36.385 --> 08:38.648
Milk first, and stir.

08:38.779 --> 08:41.303
Your facetiousness
will not sway me

08:41.477 --> 08:45.002
from my mission
to make a world-class coffee.

08:45.133 --> 08:47.004
- [INTERCOM BEEPS]
- You're so full of it.

08:47.135 --> 08:48.397
It's instant!

08:48.528 --> 08:50.834
You know we have a
thousand-dollar machine there?

08:50.965 --> 08:52.532
- You should try it.
- Yeah, yeah.

08:52.662 --> 08:55.622
Hey, Benny.
He'll be down in five.

08:55.752 --> 08:57.798
I'm making him a coffee.

08:57.928 --> 08:59.974
At least he will appreciate it.

09:01.410 --> 09:02.585
Poor Benny.

09:02.716 --> 09:05.022
He has to like it -
he works for you.

09:05.153 --> 09:07.416
Mm-hm, yeah, very funny.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.418
He will tell me the truth.

09:09.549 --> 09:11.115
You'll see.

09:11.246 --> 09:13.857
- And he'll love it.
- Sure he will. Yep.

09:17.295 --> 09:19.515
You know, honey,
some days just...

09:22.170 --> 09:25.042
..feel special,
and today feels that way.

09:26.653 --> 09:29.612
You're not getting all
philosophical on me, are you?

09:29.743 --> 09:31.353
Nah, nah, I just...

09:33.442 --> 09:36.053
I've just got
that tingly feeling, like...

09:38.621 --> 09:41.493
..that feeling
of a change in the air.

09:41.624 --> 09:43.234
Feels like a good day.

09:46.063 --> 09:48.239
You be good at school.

09:48.370 --> 09:50.024
Learn heaps.

09:51.982 --> 09:53.505
See you later tonight.

09:53.636 --> 09:55.159
What are we doing for dinner?

09:55.290 --> 09:57.422
I'll grab something
on the way home.

09:57.553 --> 09:59.120
Something special.

09:59.250 --> 10:00.600
Something healthy.

10:04.081 --> 10:06.040
[CUTLERY CLINKS]

10:12.263 --> 10:14.701
[PENSIVE PIANO MUSIC]

10:16.267 --> 10:17.573
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

10:17.704 --> 10:19.314
Hey.

10:22.622 --> 10:24.101
Love you, Princess.

10:24.232 --> 10:25.842
Love you too, Daddy.

10:35.765 --> 10:38.072
[INDIE POP SONG
CONTINUES PLAYING]

10:43.904 --> 10:46.863
[BROODING ATMOSPHERIC MUSIC]

10:55.045 --> 10:57.744
DETECTIVE: So,
what have you seen that, um...

10:57.874 --> 11:01.399
..you would consider
to be illegal activity?

11:01.530 --> 11:03.271
[PHONES RINGING IN DISTANCE]

11:04.402 --> 11:06.274
You know, he... [SCOFFS]

11:06.404 --> 11:09.277
..he was good at hiding...

11:09.407 --> 11:11.627
..everything from me.

11:11.758 --> 11:15.109
You know,
he-he made sure that...

11:15.239 --> 11:17.328
..I saw nothing,
I heard nothing.

11:17.459 --> 11:19.156
That was...

11:19.287 --> 11:20.897
..that was Abe.

11:23.291 --> 11:27.425
I was just his driver.
He just made sure that was it.

11:28.644 --> 11:30.907
BEN:
Now, that was a fuckin' lie.

11:31.038 --> 11:33.040
I knew everything about Abe.

11:33.170 --> 11:34.824
The only thing I didn't know

11:34.955 --> 11:37.174
was his state of mind
that morning.

11:37.305 --> 11:39.611
[TRAFFIC BLARES IN DISTANCE]

11:40.874 --> 11:42.484
Nah, nah, finish your smoke.

11:44.094 --> 11:45.356
Thanks, boss.

11:45.487 --> 11:47.402
My pleasure, young Benjamin.

11:51.798 --> 11:53.277
You want one?

11:54.931 --> 11:56.280
Not here.

11:56.411 --> 11:58.239
- Sofe'll kill me.
- Mm.

11:58.369 --> 11:59.719
BEN: Sofe.

11:59.849 --> 12:01.764
Sofe left a few years ago.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.680
Clearly off his meds.

12:04.811 --> 12:08.379
[INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

12:12.906 --> 12:14.037
Well?

12:15.691 --> 12:16.736
Well?

12:17.780 --> 12:20.304
- The coffee.
- Oh! Mm.

12:28.443 --> 12:29.749
Pretty bloody good!

12:29.879 --> 12:32.708
Fuck yeah. I said that.
It's good, right?

12:32.839 --> 12:34.014
Yeah! That's good!

12:34.144 --> 12:35.798
Yeah, that's what
I said to Sofe.

12:35.929 --> 12:37.713
- It's really good.
- I said it's good

12:37.844 --> 12:39.628
and you would
tell me the truth, yeah?

12:39.759 --> 12:40.803
100.

12:41.978 --> 12:45.068
Yeah, that's good. Mmm.

12:45.199 --> 12:47.244
For instant coffee.

12:47.375 --> 12:49.507
Fuck you, instant coffee!

12:49.638 --> 12:50.987
What?

12:51.118 --> 12:53.773
Never mind. Instant coffee...
Get in the car.

12:53.903 --> 12:55.862
[BEN CHUCKLES]

12:55.992 --> 12:58.038
[INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

12:59.648 --> 13:00.910
Fuck!

13:01.041 --> 13:03.304
- Instant fuckin' coffee...
- [CAR ENGINE STARTS]

13:03.434 --> 13:05.045
- Fuck...
- [BEN LAUGHS]

13:05.175 --> 13:07.787
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

13:07.917 --> 13:10.267
[INDISTINCT POLICE RADIO
CHATTER CONTINUES]

13:17.144 --> 13:19.929
BEN: Every day
was the same routine.

13:20.060 --> 13:21.844
And today felt no different.

13:21.975 --> 13:24.542
Cops were like clockwork.

13:24.673 --> 13:26.327
It was always
a bit of cat-and-mouse

13:26.457 --> 13:27.676
with the boys in blue.

13:27.807 --> 13:29.852
POLICE RADIO:
..formal operation in progress

13:29.983 --> 13:31.027
in North Sector 26...

13:31.767 --> 13:32.812
[CHUCKLES]

13:32.942 --> 13:35.249
Morning, cocksuckers.

13:35.379 --> 13:38.382
DETECTIVE: Keep on 'em, Wannie.
Keep on 'em.

13:38.513 --> 13:41.733
These guys are so obvious
it's a fuckin' joke.

13:46.173 --> 13:48.088
Glovebox.

13:48.218 --> 13:49.785
BEN: New burner.

13:49.916 --> 13:51.526
[OPENS GLOVEBOX]

13:51.656 --> 13:55.356
Burners were how Abe talks
to his different personalities.

13:55.486 --> 13:59.360
A bit of a charade, but it's
how he manages his illness.

13:59.490 --> 14:01.753
So, what's on today, boss?
What are we doin'?

14:01.884 --> 14:04.452
- It's a big day, Benny boy.
- Oh, yeah?

14:04.582 --> 14:06.628
- A big day.
- Alright.

14:06.758 --> 14:08.412
Just lose those clowns.

14:08.543 --> 14:10.023
Yep, once we hit the traffic.

14:10.153 --> 14:11.676
DETECTIVE: Keep on 'em.

14:11.807 --> 14:13.504
[TYRES SCREECH, ENGINE REVS]

14:13.635 --> 14:14.897
DETECTIVE: Go!

14:15.028 --> 14:16.943
[ENGINE REVS]

14:17.073 --> 14:19.075
DETECTIVE: They're runnin'.
Go, go, go!

14:19.206 --> 14:20.294
[TYRES SQUEAL]

14:20.424 --> 14:23.558
DETECTIVE: Fuckin' hell! Urgh!

14:25.603 --> 14:26.866
[CHUCKLES]

14:26.996 --> 14:31.131
Now, that, young Benny Boy,
was a piece of art!

14:31.261 --> 14:34.134
And that is why you
are my driver.

14:34.264 --> 14:35.744
Thanks, boss.

14:35.875 --> 14:38.703
They may want to take a few
demerit points off your licence

14:38.834 --> 14:40.357
but well worth it.

14:40.488 --> 14:42.272
- [CHUCKLES]
- Fuck 'em.

14:44.144 --> 14:46.407
[TYRES SCREECH]

14:52.500 --> 14:54.589
So, what's the plan?

14:54.719 --> 14:56.983
The plan is already happening.

14:57.157 --> 14:59.724
See, in this business, it's all
about doing and reacting

14:59.855 --> 15:02.075
to what's happening around you.

15:02.205 --> 15:03.641
A reflex.

15:05.513 --> 15:07.819
Everything's changing, Benny.

15:07.950 --> 15:10.300
This Frankie situation...

15:10.431 --> 15:12.259
I've got to adapt.

15:15.610 --> 15:17.612
It's like a game of chess.

15:17.742 --> 15:19.657
Someone does that move
and takes a rook,

15:19.788 --> 15:22.660
so you do this move
and take a knight.

15:23.923 --> 15:26.751
The trick is
not to expose your queen...

15:27.970 --> 15:30.407
..or fuck the king.

15:30.538 --> 15:34.759
And tonight Frankie will know
who the real king is.

15:38.198 --> 15:40.200
It's about getting
that shit done.

15:41.723 --> 15:43.464
[STATIC ON RADIO CRACKLES]

15:43.594 --> 15:46.423
['AHH' BY REALBOY
PLAYS ON RADIO]

15:46.554 --> 15:51.428
♪ Being a child of abandonment
just like you

15:53.039 --> 15:57.043
♪ Forced to live
in such a sick green world

16:00.046 --> 16:03.832
♪ It's been months now
and you're all hooked on it

16:03.963 --> 16:07.227
♪ It's been years now
and you're just as hopeless

16:07.357 --> 16:11.013
♪ But you should have known
this by now... ♪

16:12.014 --> 16:16.453
I was just his driver.
He just made sure that was it.

16:16.584 --> 16:17.846
DETECTIVE: Come on, Benny.

16:17.977 --> 16:19.891
I think you can do better
than that, mate.

16:25.810 --> 16:30.293
We did stop
at a building on Fison.

16:30.424 --> 16:33.166
DETECTIVE: Who lives there
at this meeting place, Benny?

16:33.296 --> 16:35.124
No, no idea.

16:35.255 --> 16:36.734
DETECTIVE: No idea?
- No idea.

16:36.865 --> 16:38.736
I'd never been there before.

16:38.867 --> 16:41.000
BEN: Well, that was bullshit.

16:41.130 --> 16:43.741
We'd been there
plenty of times before.

16:43.872 --> 16:46.135
It was just another part
of the process.

16:48.877 --> 16:51.488
[GRUNTS]

17:00.410 --> 17:03.457
BEN: And this is Kane -

17:03.631 --> 17:07.722
Abe's most dangerous
personality.

17:07.852 --> 17:10.072
The fighter and the fixer.

17:10.203 --> 17:11.856
The killer.

17:11.987 --> 17:14.555
This was his darkness.

17:14.685 --> 17:17.558
The closest personality to him.

17:17.688 --> 17:20.517
The part of himself
he could always rely on.

17:21.736 --> 17:25.914
See, some of us are thrown
into this world by chance.

17:26.045 --> 17:27.916
But Kane...

17:28.047 --> 17:31.050
..Kane was created
for this world.

17:32.921 --> 17:35.576
A tailor-made savage.

17:38.405 --> 17:41.321
BEN: Fison Ave?
ABE: Just a tick.

17:41.451 --> 17:42.974
[LINE RINGING]

17:43.105 --> 17:45.455
I gotta deal with
this finance fucker.

17:45.629 --> 17:47.501
[SERENE CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS]

17:47.631 --> 17:50.982
BEN: Meet Richard. Another one
of his personalities.

17:51.113 --> 17:53.550
The part that does
all the finances.

17:53.681 --> 17:55.944
Washes the cash,
turns it legal.

17:56.075 --> 17:59.861
Every successful crime boss
needs a Richard.

18:01.123 --> 18:03.386
[LINE RINGING]

18:03.517 --> 18:05.040
Can you believe this guy?

18:05.171 --> 18:07.477
Ignoring me
for over a week now.

18:07.608 --> 18:09.349
Thinks he's above me.

18:12.178 --> 18:14.223
[LINE RINGING]

18:14.354 --> 18:17.661
Guy's either got big balls
or he's a fuckin' idiot.

18:17.792 --> 18:19.359
Or he's both.

18:19.489 --> 18:21.230
[CHUCKLES]

18:21.361 --> 18:23.537
[PHONE RINGS]

18:23.667 --> 18:24.973
[PHONE STOPS]

18:25.104 --> 18:28.542
BEN: The problem is,
Richard wasn't answering Abe.

18:28.672 --> 18:30.979
Richard had gone rogue.

18:31.066 --> 18:34.809
And it was like he'd created
his own separate life.

18:34.939 --> 18:37.681
To Abe, these personalities
were as real

18:37.812 --> 18:39.944
as the person
sittin' next to you.

18:40.075 --> 18:41.990
[DISCONNECT TONE]

18:43.905 --> 18:46.037
I fuckin' bankroll this maggot

18:46.168 --> 18:48.910
and he thinks he can
walk away and cut me out,

18:49.040 --> 18:51.478
just flush me
like a fuckin' turd!

18:53.219 --> 18:55.699
You want me to chat to him?

18:55.830 --> 18:58.180
BEN: As if that'd ever happen.

18:58.311 --> 19:00.443
Nah, it's well beyond that,
Benny.

19:01.662 --> 19:03.185
Well beyond chatting.

19:05.361 --> 19:07.624
[LINE RINGING]

19:07.755 --> 19:09.409
STAN: [ON PHONE] Boss.
- Stano.

19:09.539 --> 19:11.062
Meet us for a catch-up.

19:11.193 --> 19:12.499
No problem.

19:13.935 --> 19:16.067
- Yeah, you got the address?
- Fison Ave.

19:16.198 --> 19:17.460
How long?

19:17.591 --> 19:19.201
- 15.
- 15.

19:19.332 --> 19:21.290
- Alright, see you there.
- Righto.

19:31.909 --> 19:34.260
Some days, Benny, you just
gotta show these pricks

19:34.390 --> 19:36.131
who's holding the aces.

19:39.178 --> 19:41.876
No more fuckin' around
with these clowns.

19:43.312 --> 19:45.967
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

19:46.097 --> 19:47.664
[HEAVY MUSIC
PLAYS ON HEADPHONES]

19:47.795 --> 19:50.885
BEN: You see, Abe saw the world
as one big hostile place.

19:51.015 --> 19:53.104
Hostility attracts hostility.

19:53.235 --> 19:54.410
[TYRES SCREECH]

19:54.497 --> 19:55.890
What the fuck?!

19:56.020 --> 19:58.240
